         b'td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br>\nI do r'
         b'esearch into "designing in" security and other properties of\nsys'
         b'tems using a combination of program analysis, algorithm design a'
         b'nd\nformal specification. I like to think that this is important,'
         b' fun,\nexciting and useful. A lot of people agree with me about\nt'
         b'hose qualities. <br>\n\n\n\n\n\n<br>\nFor BSc (and even MSci) I thi'
         b'nk the project should be more fun and\nexciting and less obscure '
         b'and purely technical. This is why I always\ntry to find out what '
         b'the student wants to do. In the past this has\nworked well (mostl'
         b'y) and a large proportion of my past students have\nmanaged disti'
         b'nction level projects. That being said, none of them have\nas yet'
         b' won the project prize, but maybe that changes this year?<br>\n<b'
         b'r>\nThese are some projects I have supervised in the past:<br>\n<u'
         b'l>\n  <li>face recognition system</li>\n  <li>footprint recognitio'
         b'n system</li>\n  <li>information flow analyser for a While langua'
         b'ge</li>\n  <li>real-time laptop music notation generation for gui'
         b'tar-players</li>\n  <li>electronic elections</li>\n  <li>reactive '
         b'system specification case study: watering a garden</li>\n  <li>in'
         b'formation flow measurer for a while language</li>\n  <li>browser '
         b'for a PDA</li>\n  <li>3D drafts</li>\n  <li>keyboard music generat'
         b'ion via number notation</li>\n  <li>floating security type system'
         b' for a While language<br>\n  </li>\n</ul>\nMy idea is to do somethi'
         b'ng imaginative and challenging that you are\ninterested in. I wil'
         b"l expect you to do all the work and I won't be\nspelling it out t"
         b'o you step by step. If you want an easy time I am\nprobably not t'
         b'he supervisor for you. But if you like a challenge and\nwant a pr'
         b'oject you can be proud of on your CV, come and see me\n(preferabl'
         b'y in office hours).<br>\n<br>\nMy motto: &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbs'
         b'p; &nbsp; &nbsp; <span\n style="color: rgb(153, 0, 0);"><span\n st'
         b'yle="font-family: LucidaTypewriter;">We do the right project 4 U</sp'
         b'an></span><br>\n<table>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td><!-- Begin c'
         b'omment\n\n      <table border="0" cellpadding="4" style="width: 10'
         b'0%;">\n        <tbody>\n          <tr>\n            <td align="left'
         b'"><b><font face="Arial,Helvetica" size="-1">DC(B)01</font></b></'
         b'td>\n            <td align="center"><b><font face="Arial,Helvetic'
         b'a" size="-1">Interactive\noperating system algorithms</font></b><'
         b'/td>\n            <td align="left"><font face="Arial,Helvetica" s'
         b'ize="-1">There\nare a number\nof algorithms used in the implementa'
         b'tion of operating systems. The aim\nof\nthis project is to create '
         b'a visual, interactive program with a nice,\neasy\nto use, intuitiv'
         b'e interface that demonstrates a range of these\nalgorithms.\nThe p'
         b'roject is straightforward and open-ended and a good student will'
